    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1875-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1875-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="180" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                <head>No. 479.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Gibbs</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-09-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 14,
                            1875</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch No. 14, under date
                        of the 18th ultimo, relating to the death and funeral ceremonies of Rear-Ad
                        mind Napoleon Collins, U. S. N., I have to request that you will convey to
                        the Peruvian government the thanks of that of the United States for the
                        signal courtesies extended, and for the sympathy shown on the occasion.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                        Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
